'''Patiala Shahi Pagg''' ([[turban]]) is a turban style based upon the turban style of old kings. This is also known as ''Tehdi Pagg''. It was also known as Kharbuja Pagg.It is the most common among all turbans and usually worn in the north part [[India]], specially in [[Punjab]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.apnapatiala.com/patiala-special/the-punjabi-pagg-and-the-evolution-of-the-patiala-shahi-pagg/|title=The Punjabi Pagg and the Evolution of the Patiala Shahi Pagg- Apna Patiala|website=www.apnapatiala.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://patialashahiturban.com|title=Home - Patiala Shahi Turban|website=Patiala Shahi Turban}}</ref>

The design of this turban is really royal. There are two parts of this turban. One is left and other is right. Both look similar, but comparatively to one side, other looks inverted.Its completely different from Morni or Pochvi Dastar which is mostly of pointed shape

