'''Sanctum''' is a sacred place, in a [[shrine]] within a [[temple]] or [[church (building)|church]]. It also refers to a sacred place of [[pilgrimage]].
The Latin word ''[[wikt:sanctum|sanctum]]'' is the neuter form of the adjective "[[sacred|holy]]".
